	<http://purl.org/dc/terms/hasPart> "How two women called Juliana and Barbara, went on a pilgrimage to Jerusalem, were attached by robbers who stole their provisions; and how, when the thieves tried to eat them, the Virgin Mary turned the bread into stones upon which the thieves broke their teeth; and how the thieves repented and restored twofold what they had stolen from the women, when the Virgin Mary had healed their wounded mouths and mended their broken teeth" ;
