	<http://purl.org/dc/terms/hasPart> "How three Arabs set sail for Rif, and were overtaken by a storm which sank their boat and hurled them into the water; how two of them appealed to the Virgin Mary for help, and were saved by her, whilst the third, who jeered at their prayers and called upon Muhammad the Prophet, was swallowed up by a crocodile; and how the men who were saved paid their vow and sent a camel-load of dates to the Monastery of Kalman, where there was a church dedicated to the Virgin Mary" ;
	<http://www.cidoc-crm.org/cidoc-crm/P57_has_number_of_parts> 0 .
